  "response_text": "At night, a brightly lit candy store sits on a wet street, its lights reflecting on the pavement. The storefront has large display windows outlined with rows of small bulbs, glowing red neon signs in the windows, and a rectangular sign above the entrance that appears to read “Candy Store.” Two people stand near the doorway on the sidewalk. A low, open red roadster rolls in from the right and stops in front of the shop, its shiny body catching the neon reflections.\n\nInside the car is a young blond man with medium-length feathered hair. He wears a dark satin-like jacket with striped cuffs over a light shirt. In a close view, he looks down and carefully fusses with his hair, lifting both hands to smooth and arrange it. His expression is serious and focused, as if trying to look just right. He then leans forward and gets out of the car.\n\nBack outside the candy store, the red car fills the foreground while the glowing storefront fills the background. The young man climbs out, stands beside the open car, and looks toward the shop entrance. He straightens himself and moves toward the door.\n\nInside the candy store, a young blonde woman stands behind the counter. She has long, neatly styled blonde hair pulled back, and she wears a pale pink or white blouse with a wide collar and ruffled front, suggesting a shop-worker uniform. The background is warm and colorful, with blurred candy displays and bright decorative lights. She looks ahead with a calm, attentive expression.\n\nThe young man enters through the doorway, framed by the bright strips of lights on either side. He walks in from the dark street toward the shop interior, still wearing his shiny jacket and light shirt. The woman behind the counter smiles warmly when she sees him. His head and shoulders briefly pass in front of her, partly blocking the view, and then she is visible again, smiling directly toward him. Her expression softens, then she glances downward toward the counter.\n\nA hand p